  "prompt": "What can I do with an infant at Walt Disney World?",
  "response": "Walt Disney World is a fantastic destination for families with infants, offering a variety of experiences that cater to young children. Here are some suggestions for activities and tips for visiting with an infant:\n\n### Attractions and Rides\n1. **Gentle Rides**: Many rides are suitable for infants, including:\n   - **It's a Small World** (Magic Kingdom)\n   - **Dumbo the Flying Elephant** (Magic Kingdom)\n   - **The Many Adventures of Winnie the Pooh** (Magic Kingdom)\n   - **The Seas with Nemo & Friends** (Epcot)\n   - **Frozen Ever After** (Epcot)\n   - **The Carousel of Progress** (Magic Kingdom)\n\n2. **Character Meet and Greets**: You can take photos with beloved Disney characters. Infants may not fully engage, but it\u2019s a memorable experience for the family.\n\n3. **Parades and Shows**: Enjoy parades and stage shows that are visually stimulating and entertaining for little ones.\n\n4. **Animal Experiences**: At Disney\u2019s Animal Kingdom, you can explore the lush environments and see animals, which can be captivating for infants.\n\n### Relaxation and Breaks\n1. **Baby Care Centers**: Each park has a Baby Care Center equipped with changing tables, nursing rooms, and feeding areas. These centers provide a quiet place to take a break.\n\n2. **Stroller Rentals**: Consider renting a stroller to make it easier to navigate the parks with your infant. You can also bring your own stroller.\n\n3. **Quiet Spots**: Look for shaded areas or gardens to take breaks and let your infant relax.\n\n### Dining\n1. **Kid-Friendly Restaurants**: Many restaurants have high chairs and kid-friendly menus. Consider dining at places like:\n   - **The Crystal Palace** (Magic Kingdom) - character dining with Winnie the Pooh.\n   - **Garden Grill** (Epcot) - rotating restaurant with character interactions.\n\n2. **Bringing Snacks**: You can bring snacks and formula/baby food into the parks. Just be mindful of any restrictions.\n\n### General Tips\n1. **Timing**: Plan your visit around your infant\u2019s schedule. Consider going during nap times to avoid meltdowns.\n\n2. **Stay Hydrated**: Keep both yourself and your infant hydrated, especially if it\u2019s a hot day.\n\n3. **Pack Wisely**: Bring necessary items like diapers, wipes, a change of clothes, and any comfort items your infant may need.\n\n4. **Take Advantage of Rider Switch**: If you're traveling with older children, use the Rider Switch program, allowing one adult to wait with the infant while the other rides.\n\n5. **Use Disney Genie+**: Consider using the Genie+ service to help minimize wait times for attractions that are suitable for your infant.\n\n### Conclusion\nWhile your infant may not be able to enjoy everything, the sights, sounds, and overall atmosphere of Walt Disney World can be magical for the entire family. With careful planning and the right approach, you can create wonderful memories together!",
